      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough, but doesn't that imply that \"geopolitics\" is basically just a justification for ignoring human rights? if we always prioritize \"stability\" and \"security liabilities\" over stopping actual massacres, aren't we basically saying that the realpolitik approach is the only \"rational\" one, while humanitarian concerns are just secondary or even counter-productive to actual statecraft?",
